=== GLOBAL RESPONSE WRAPPER ===

All API responses follow a unified response structure:

{
timestamp: string,
status: number,
message: string,
data: any
}

Important:
- The actual payload is always inside the "data" field.

Example:

Login Response:
{
timestamp: "...",
status: 200,
message: "Operation Successful",
data: {
user: {...},
token: "JWT"
}
}


============================================================

You MUST:

- Create a generic ApiResponse<T> type:
interface ApiResponse<T> {
timestamp: string;
status: number;
message: string;
data: T;
}

- Unwrap response.data.data inside Axios interceptor
OR
- Handle wrapper inside services consistently

- Implement global error handling based on:
- status
- message

=== DOMAIN MODELS ===

User:
- id
- firstname
- lastname
- email
- role (ADMIN / USER)

Area:
- id
- areaName
- locationDetails

Department:
- id
- deptName
- parentDepartment (nullable)

Employee:
- id
- employeeCode
- name
- status (Active / Inactive)
- area
- department

Shift:
- id
- shiftName
- startTime
- endTime
- lateThreshold
- earlyLeaveThreshold

Schedule:
- id
- employee
- shift
- dayOfWeek

Device:
- id
- serialNumber
- deviceName
- ipAddress
- port
- status (ONLINE / OFFLINE)
- area

LeaveType:
- id
- typeName

LeaveRequest:
- id
- employee
- leaveType
- startDate
- endDate
- status (PENDING / APPROVED / REJECTED)

